<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?><?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" href="..\config8\suzuki.xsl" ?><!DOCTYPE suzuki [<!ENTITY % sdatacharaents SYSTEM "..\config8\sdatacharaents.txt">%sdatacharaents;]><suzuki><manual>
<section sectnbr = "1F">
<servcat sctnbr = "01" scnbr = "06">
<configtype typenbr = "0">
<servinfotype sitcode = "6">
<servinfo servinfosgmlid = "AENCP70A1606005" svcinfotypenbr = "08" svcinfoqualnbr = "01" page = "2" supplyoff = "1" modify = "1">
<title>
Cooling System Refilling
</title>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENCP70A1606004">Cooling System Draining</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<attention1>
<ptxt>
To avoid getting burned, do not remove radiator cap while engine and radiator are still hot. Scalding fluid and steam can gush out under pressure if cap is taken off too soon.
</ptxt>
</attention1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Fill reservoir (1) with coolant up to “FULL” mark (2).
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install reservoir cap (3) on reservoir (1).
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A161006.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "54.091mm" ver = "01" gw = "199" gh = "137"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Fill radiator with coolant up to bottom of radiator filler neck and install radiator cap.
</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>
Recommended coolant
</title>
<ptxt>
SUZUKI super long life coolant (coolant color: Blue)
</ptxt>
</spec>
<spec>
<title>
Coolant specification
</title>
<ptxt>
Freezing temperature: –36 &#176;C (–33 &#176;F)
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Antifreeze / anti-corrosion coolant concentration: 50%
</ptxt>
</spec>
<spec>
<title>
Coolant capacity
</title>
<ptxt>
M/T model:
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Engine, radiator and heater: 3.8 liters (8.03/6.69 US/Imp pt.)
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Reservoir: 0.7 liters (1.48/1.23 US/Imp pt.)
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Total: 4.5 liters (9.51/7.92 US/Imp pt.)
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
<ptxt>
CVT model:
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Engine, radiator and heater: 3.9 liters (8.24/6.86 US/Imp pt.)
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Reservoir: 0.7 liters (1.48/1.23 US/Imp pt.)
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Total: 4.6 liters (9.72/8.09 US/Imp pt.)
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</spec>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Run engine at idle speed.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Run engine until radiator fan motor is operated.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Stop engine and wait until engine comes cooled down to avoid getting burned.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Add coolant to radiator up to bottom of radiator filler neck, and install radiator cap.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Repeat Step 4) through 7).
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Confirm that coolant level in reservoir is at “FULL” mark. If coolant is insufficient, add coolant.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Check for coolant leaks. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENCP70A1606003"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
</servinfo>
</servinfotype>
</configtype>
</servcat>
</section></manual></suzuki>
